{"sessionKey":"42nd1stsed_01","paragraphs":[{"html":"<a name=\"StartOfColumns\"></a><b><i>TIME</i></b><i> <b>� 6:30 p.m.</b></i>","index":"00000","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>LOCATION � Winnipeg, Manitoba</i></b>","index":"00001","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>CHAIRPERSON � Mr. Dennis Smook (La&nbsp;V�rendrye)</i></b>","index":"00002","speaker":"Dennis Smook"},{"html":"<b><i>VICE-CHAIRPERSON �</i></b><i> <b>Mr. Doyle Piwniuk (Turtle\nMountain)</b></i>","index":"00003","speaker":"Doyle Piwniuk"},{"html":"<b><i>ATTENDANCE � 11��� QUORUM � 6</i></b>","index":"00004","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Members of the\nCommittee present:</i>","index":"00005","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Hon. Messrs.\nEichler, Pedersen</i>","index":"00006","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Mses. Adams,\nGordon, Messrs. Guenter, Isleifson, Lindsey, Moses, Piwniuk, Smook, Wasyliw</i>","index":"00007","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>MATTERS UNDER CONSIDERATION:</i></b>","index":"00008","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Bill&nbsp;22�The\nBusiness Registration, Supervision and Ownership Transparency Act (Various Acts\nAmended)</i>","index":"00009","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>* * *</b>","index":"00010","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Clerk Assistant (Mr. Andrea Signorelli):</b> Good evening. Will the\nStanding Committee on Social and Economic Development please come to order. ","index":"00011","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Before the committee can proceed with the business before it, it\nmust elect a new Chairperson. ","index":"00012","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any nominations for this position?","index":"00013","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Len Isleifson (Brandon East):</b> I nominate Mr.&nbsp;Smook.","index":"00014","speaker":"Len Isleifson"},{"html":"<b>Clerk Assistant:</b> Mr. Smook has been nominated. ","index":"00015","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any other nominations?","index":"00016","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Hearing no other nominations, Mr. Smook, will you please take the\nChair.","index":"00017","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b>� Our next item of business is the election of a\nVice-Chairperson.� ","index":"00018","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any nominations?","index":"00019","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Audrey Gordon (Southdale):</b> I'd like to nominate Mr. Piwniuk.","index":"00020","speaker":"Audrey Gordon"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Mr. Piwniuk has been nominated.� ","index":"00021","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Are there any other\nnominations? ","index":"00022","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Hearing no other nominations, Mr. Piwniuk is elected\nVice-Chairperson. ","index":"00023","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This meeting has been called to consider Bill&nbsp;22, The\nBusiness Registration, Supervision and Ownership Transparency Act (Various Acts\nAmended). We have one presenter registered to speak tonight, as noted on the\nlist of presenters before you. ","index":"00024","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Public presentation guide�oh, before we continue, I'd just like\nto inform the committee that, as part of ongoing efforts to update the\nLegislative Assembly educational video series, the proceedings of the committee\nwill be filmed from the gallery this evening. Thank you. ","index":"00025","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Before we proceed with presentations, we do have a number of\nother items and points of information to consider. ","index":"00026","speaker":""},{"html":"����� First of all, if there is anyone else in the audience who would\nlike to make a presentation this evening, please register with staff at the\nentrance of the room. ","index":"00027","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Also, for the information of all presenters, while written\nversions of presentations are not required, if you are going to accompany your\npresentation with written materials, we ask that you provide 20 copies. If you\nneed help with photocopying, please speak with our staff. ","index":"00028","speaker":""},{"html":"����� As well, in accordance with our rules, a time limit of 10 minutes\nhas been allotted for presentations, with another 5 minutes allowed for\nquestions from committee members. ","index":"00029","speaker":""},{"html":"����� If a presenter is not in attendance, their name will be�their\nname is called�when their name is called, they will be dropped to the bottom of\nthe list. If the presenter is not in attendance when their name is called a\nsecond time, they will be removed from the presenters list. ","index":"00030","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Prior to proceeding with public presentations, I would like to\nadvise members of the public regarding the process of speaking in committee.\nThe proceedings of our meetings are recorded in order to provide a verbatim\ntranscript. Each time someone wishes to speak, whether it be an MLA or a\npresenter, I first have to say the person's name. This is the signal for the\nHansard recorder to turn the mics on and off. ","index":"00031","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank you for your patience. We will now proceed with public\npresentations. ","index":"00032","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> I will now call on Galen�Gaile Whalen Enns.\nGaile Whalen Enns?","index":"00033","speaker":""},{"html":"It appears that our presenter is not here. She will\nbe moved to the bottom of the list and I will call her again since she's the\nonly one presenter. ","index":"00034","speaker":""},{"html":"Gaile Whalen Enns. Gaile Whalen Enns?","index":"00035","speaker":""},{"html":"I'm�she will be now dropped from the list. ","index":"00036","speaker":""},{"html":"That concludes the list of presenters I have before\nme.","index":"00037","speaker":""},{"html":"Are there any other persons in attendance who wish to\nmake a presentation? ","index":"00038","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Seeing none, that concludes public presentations. ","index":"00039","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>* * *</b>","index":"00040","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> We will now proceed with clause by clause of\nBill 22.","index":"00041","speaker":""},{"html":"<span lang=\"EN-US\">Does the minister responsible for\nBill 22 have an opening statement? </span>","index":"00042","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Blaine Pedersen (Minister of Growth, Enterprise and Trade):</b>\nJust a very short statement; general background on Bill 22. ","index":"00043","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"The bill amends four different\nacts, including The Corporations Act, The Business Names Registration Act, The\nPartnership Act and The Cooperatives Act. ","index":"00044","speaker":""},{"html":"The amendments can be divided into\nthree categories: amendments to reconcile business registration and reporting\nrequirements with those in other Canadian jurisdictions. Secondly, amendments\nto introduce beneficial ownership requirements. These are requirements for\ncorporations to maintain a register of individuals with significant control of\nthe corporation. And thirdly, amendments to transfer administrative\nresponsibilities related to business registration for co-operatives from the\nFinancial Institutions Regulation Branch to the Companies Office and the\nestablishment of a new superintendent of co-operatives.","index":"00045","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank you, Mr. Chair.","index":"00046","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> We thank the minister for his statement. ","index":"00047","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Does the critic from the official opposition have an opening\nstatement?","index":"00048","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Jamie Moses (St. Vital):</b> Thank you, Mr.&nbsp;Chairperson,\nfor having us here together today and thank you to the minister. ","index":"00049","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"Reading through the changes to\nthe bill, just wanted to highlight a few areas of concern were around the\nchanges of the registrar to the superintendent role; worried about some of the\nconcerns that it might not be able to provide as much support to co-operatives\nthat are being formed and therefore, you know, might leave some people\ndisadvantaged when they're looking to set up their co‑operatives. Worried\nabout that aspect of it.","index":"00050","speaker":""},{"html":"The second part is a little bit\nabout the trans�parency when it comes to corporate�corporations; worried that\nthat 25&nbsp;per&nbsp;cent shareholder for being�transparency in terms of\nvoting rights. Maybe that threshold might be a little bit higher, maybe it\nshould�be too low to provide additional transparency for corporations.","index":"00051","speaker":""},{"html":"But overall, looking at the bill,\nwe will�I look forward to a good discussion as we go line by line through the\nbill and, you know, keeping in mind that we want to have the best interests of\nall Manitobans as we go through it.","index":"00052","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Thank you.","index":"00053","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> We thank the member. ","index":"00054","speaker":""},{"html":"����� During the consideration of a bill, the preamble, the enacting\nclause and the title are postponed until all other clauses have been considered\nin their proper order. Also if there is agreement from the committee, the Chair\nwill call clauses in blocks that conform to pages, with the understanding that\nwe will stop at any particular clause or clauses where members may have\ncomments, questions or amendments to propose. Is that agreed? <i>[Agreed] </i>","index":"00055","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b> (18:40)","index":"00056","speaker":""},{"html":"Clause 1 and 2�pass; clause\n3�pass; clause 4 and 5�pass; clauses 6 and 7�pass; clauses 8 and 9�pass;\nclauses 10 through 13�pass; clause 14�pass; clauses&nbsp;15 through 17��pass;\nclauses 18 through 21�pass; clauses 22 through 27�pass; clauses 28 through\n33�pass; clauses 34 and 35�pass; clauses 36 through 38�pass; clauses 39 through\n41�pass; clauses 42 through 44�pass; clauses 45 and 46�pass.","index":"00057","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Shall clause 47�","index":"00058","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>An Honourable Member:</b> No.","index":"00059","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> No? I hear a no. ","index":"00060","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We have an amendment in�<i>[interjection]</i>","index":"00061","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> I move ","index":"00062","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<i>THAT Clause&nbsp;47 of the Bill be amended in the proposed\nsubsection&nbsp;21.1(7) of <b>The Corporations Act</b> by striking out \"</i>or<i>\"\nat the end of clause&nbsp;(d) and adding the following after clause&nbsp;(d):</i>","index":"00063","speaker":""},{"html":"(d.1)&nbsp;a corporation without share capital; or","index":"00064","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> It is moved by the honourable Minister of\nGrowth, Enterprise and Trade (Mr.&nbsp;Pedersen)","index":"00065","speaker":""},{"html":"That the business�no, no, no, no�<i>THAT Clause 47 of the\nBill be amended in the proposed</i>�","index":"00066","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>An Honourable Member:</b> Dispense.","index":"00067","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Dispense?","index":"00068","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Dispense.","index":"00069","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Okay. The amendment is in order. The&nbsp;floor\nis open for questions. ","index":"00070","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> Just wanted to ask the minister for a description of\nthe change and why it's so important to come in now.","index":"00071","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> Because this is for non-profit companies. They\ndon't have shareholders that have value in the company, and this was missed in\nthe original version of the bill and it should have been there in the\noriginal�in the version that was brought in June�in May�in June. So this is\njust correcting that. There's no need for non-profit companies because they\ndon't have shareholders, per se, that have value.","index":"00072","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> And this is for any registered and non‑profits\nor charities in Manitoba registered, is that correct? ","index":"00073","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> Yes. ","index":"00074","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> And when did you realize the change was coming; what\nneeded to be added and amended to this bill? This was introduced in the spring\nand it's coming in now. Just wanted to know of the timeline of how that\noccurred. ","index":"00075","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> Sometime over the�just hold on.","index":"00076","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"����� So during the summer, upon review, the staff realized that this\nshould've been in the original bill and this�the Canada Business Corporations\nAct, the federal act does not include non-profits, so it excludes non-profits.\nSo this is in line with what the federal bill&nbsp;is. ","index":"00077","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Is the committee ready for the\nquestion?","index":"00078","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Question.","index":"00079","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> The question before the committee is as\nfollows.","index":"00080","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Amendment�pass; clause 47 as amended�pass; clauses 48 and\n49�pass; clauses 50 and 51�pass; clauses 52 through 54�pass; clauses 55 through\n58�pass; clauses 59 and 60�pass; clause 61�pass; clauses&nbsp;62 and 63�pass.","index":"00081","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Shall class 64 pass?","index":"00082","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>An Honourable Member:</b> No.","index":"00083","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> I hear a no.","index":"00084","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> I move","index":"00085","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<i>THAT Clause 64 of the Bill be replaced with the following:</i>","index":"00086","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Coming into force�proclamation</i>","index":"00087","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>64(1)\n�Subject to subsection (2), this Act comes into force on a day to be fixed by\nproclamation.</i>","index":"00088","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Coming into force�</i>in force�<i>April 8, 2020 </i>","index":"00089","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>64(2)\n�Sections 10, 19, 21, 23, 45 to 50, 52 and 53 come into force on a day to be\nfixed by proclamation or on April 8, 2020, whichever occurs first.</i>","index":"00090","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson: </b>It has been moved by the Honourable Mr.\nPedersen","index":"00091","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>THAT�</i>the�<i>THAT Clause 64 of</i>�","index":"00092","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Dispense.","index":"00093","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b><span style=\"color:windowtext;\nfont-weight:normal\"> Dispense? Dispense.</span>","index":"00094","speaker":""},{"html":"<span style=\"color:windowtext;font-weight:normal\">����� The\namendment is in order. The floor is open for questions.</span>","index":"00095","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> I wanted to ask the minister why the date changed\nfrom January to April, why to extend it? Why the rush to pass it now if it's\ngoing to be delayed 'til April?","index":"00096","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> When this bill was introduced,\nit was drafted on the basis that it would likely receive royal assent in June\nof 2019�pardon me.","index":"00097","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"The coming into force provision\nprovided for the whole bill to come into force on January 1st, 2020. This\nwould've provided corporations with over six months of notice to prepare for\nthe new requirements to maintain a register of individuals with significant\ncontrol.","index":"00098","speaker":""},{"html":"The January 1 date also would\nhave brought the business registration changes into force on the same date by\nwhich Manitoba is obliged�is obligated to reconcile business registration\nrequirements with its New West trade partners.","index":"00099","speaker":""},{"html":"As this bill is now expected to\nreceive royal assent&nbsp;&nbsp;on October 11th, in accordance with the Sessional&nbsp;Order,\nwe are proposing to change the coming into force date for the beneficial\nownership changes to April 8, 2020 which will maintain a roughly six‑month\nnotice period. ","index":"00100","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b> (18:50)","index":"00101","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We are proposing to change the coming into force date for the\nremainder of the act to be set by proclamation as there is some uncertainty as\nto whether or not all jurisdictions will be able to make the necessary IT\nupgrades to facilitate reconciliation of business registration and reporting\nprocesses by January 1st.","index":"00102","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Once Manitoba and its New West trade partners have determined a\nfinal date and proclamation will be issued to set the coming into force date,\nthen we will�we are hopeful that this will happen early in the new year. ","index":"00103","speaker":""},{"html":"����� So, in layman's terms on�we need to give corporations six months\nadvance notice so that they can begin to register their share�major\nshareholders and also there is some IT issues apparently in Alberta that\nthey're not sure they can make the January 1st. ","index":"00104","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We were concerned that we were going to not make January 1st, but\nwe believe we'll be ready to do the common registration portion of this bill by\nApril&nbsp;8th, and as soon as the other three provinces within the New West\nPartnership are ready to go then we can proclaim that part. ","index":"00105","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses: </b>So, just to clarify in terms of a New West trade deal\nportion of it, how certain are we that the other jurisdictions are going to be\nready for that date? Like, how do we know April is the correct time frame? ","index":"00106","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"����� Like, what if they need more time or is this something that we\nwill need to look at delaying again, or is that the right time frame for moving\nforward with this bill? ","index":"00107","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> We believe it's a adequate time frame. In fact, we\nare somewhat confident we can do it before then. Staff from GET has been in\nconversation with the other departments from across the west, the other three\nprovinces. ","index":"00108","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"����� And to date, it's only been Alberta that has expressed concerns\nabout needing some extra time. Saskatchewan and British Columbia are ready to\ngo now. And so we feel that this will be ready to go then. And as it comes into\nforce from proclamation, it could be extended if necessary, but this allows us\nto set the proclamation date. ","index":"00109","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> And then, just, again, to clarify, just to go over\nthat, six months is about the time frame, October to April. It's not quite�I\nmean, do we want to give businesses additional time, like, would May make more\nsense, for�to give us a full six months? ","index":"00110","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"����� Or is this even pushing them to not be prepared for when this\ncomes into�in force in April, even�because it is still under six months right\nnow. ","index":"00111","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> Because the bill was originally intended to pass\nin last June, 2019, companies have already had lots of adequate notice about\nthis. And so they were prepared for it to pass in June 9�of June of 2019, so\nthey've already had time to do this, and this�there's more than adequate time\nfor them to register. ","index":"00112","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Moses:</b> One last follow-up. ","index":"00113","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"����� And I understand that, and then it leads me to the next question.\nIs�if they have adequate time, well, then why not just stick with the January\n1st? ","index":"00114","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Pedersen:</b> It's just�it makes it easier as the bill�to pass\nthe bill. ","index":"00115","speaker":"Blaine Pedersen"},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Is the committee ready for the question?","index":"00116","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Question. ","index":"00117","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Question. The question before the committee is\nas follows.","index":"00118","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Amendment�pass; clause 64 as amended�pass; enacting clause�pass;\ntitle�pass. Bill as amended be reported. ","index":"00119","speaker":""},{"html":"����� The hour being 6:54, what is the will of the committee? ","index":"00120","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Rise. ","index":"00121","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nChairperson:</b> Committee rise.","index":"00122","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>COMMITTEE\nROSE AT:</i></b><i> 6:55 p.m.</i> ","index":"00123","speaker":""}]}